      • filterNullableStatuses

        @Nonnull
T filterNullableStatuses(@Nullable
                                  Predicate<String> statusFilter)
        Creates a narrowed-down, independent collection of fund acceptance data for fund acceptance statuses passing a given predicate. A null fund acceptance status is one possible argument to the given predicate.
        Parameters:
        statusFilter - the predicate.
        Returns:
        the new collection.

      • filterStatuses

        @Nonnull
T filterStatuses(@Nullable
                          Predicate<String> statusFilter)
        Creates a narrowed-down, independent collection of fund acceptance data for fund acceptance statuses passing a given predicate. Null fund acceptance statuses implicitly do not pass the filter and the predicate is not even invoked in this case.
        Parameters:
        statusFilter - the predicate.
        Returns:
        the new collection.

      • getWithStatuses

        @Nonnull
T getWithStatuses(@Nullable
                           Iterable<String> statuses)
        Creates a narrowed-down, independent collection of fund acceptance data for given fund acceptance statuses. Null can be passed as a possible status.
        Parameters:
        statuses - the statuses.
        Returns:
        the new collection.
